<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-21T09:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-21T09:40:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1759.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-21T10:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 21, 1915—10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>According to Government announcements confirmed from other sources, Feliu
                            and fifty-two followers have surrendered with arms at Santiago and Feliu
                            is to leave first opportunity for abroad. Government has also announced
                            that rebel leaders in east will not be granted guaranties.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>